<a name="Running pp2html">

<H1>Running pp2html
</H1>


<P>
To run <CODE>pp2html</CODE> you need an input file in PerlPoint format (see <A HREF="slide0005.htm#PerlPoint Syntax">PerlPoint Syntax</A> and eventually an <A HREF="slide0106.htm#Option Files">option file</A> to specify all the options you want to use.
</P>


<P>
All possible options are described in the <A HREF="slide0058.htm#Options">Options</A> chapter.
</P>


<P>
Here are some examples for calls to <CODE>pp2html</CODE>:
</P>


<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=80%><TR><TD bgcolor="#e5e5e5"><PRE>
<FONT COLOR="#000000">
 # Change to the directory where the input file is
 # located and start pp2html:

 pp2html input.pp

 pp2html -target_dir ./slides -title=&quot;PerlPoint&quot; input.pp

 pp2html @my_options.cfg input.pp

 pp2html -style big_blue -style_dir /home/PP/styles input.pp
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR></TABLE>
